Functions in the Term Lib:
- term.getSize(max)
	* gets the minimum or maximum size of the output
	* return values:
		- the horizontal size of the output (number)
		- the vertical size of the output (number)
	* parameters:
		- max: true to get the maximum size, false to get the minimum (boolean) [optional]
- term.clear()
	* clears the output
- term.clearLine(line)
	* clears a line of the output
	* parameters:
		- line: the number of line to clear (number) [optional]
- term.getCursorPos()
	* gets the cursor position
	* return values:
		- the horizontal position of the cursor (number)
		- the vertical position of the cursor (number)
- term.setCursorPos(x, y)
	* moves the cursor to the specified position
	* parameters:
		- x: the horizontal position of the cursor (number)
		- y: the vertical position of the cursor (number)
- term.setCursorBlink(b)
	* sets the cursor blinking mode
	* parameters:
		- b: true to make the cursor blink, false to make it stop (boolean)
- term.scroll(n)
	* scrolls the screen vertically, moving the text up
	* parameters:
		- n: the number of lines to scroll (number)
- term.write(text, wrap)
	* writes text to the screen
	* return values:
		- the number of lines used to write (number)
	* parameters:
		- text: the text to write (any type)
		- wrap: boolean indicating if the text should wrap when it gets to the end of the line (boolean) [optional]
- term.print(...)
	* prints text on the screen, adding a new line at the end
	* return values:
		- the number of lines printed (number)
	* parameters:
		- any value to print
- term.read(replaceChar, history, max)
	* gets user input
	* return values:
		- the text entered by the user (string)
	* parameters:
		- replaceChar: character to use as replacement for the entered text (string) [optional]
		- history: history table (table) [optional]
		- max: maximum number of characters to read (number) [optional]